    "what_description": "Grewia speciosa is a flowering plant species in the family Malvaceae, native to tropical Africa. It is a shrub or small tree, growing up to 12 meters tall, with a broad, spreading crown and a greyish-brown, fissured trunk. The leaves are alternate, simple, and ovate, measuring 10-20 cm long, with a rounded base and a pointed apex, bearing 3-5 pairs of lateral veins. The flowers are showy, with five petals, measuring 5-8 cm long, and are borne in clusters at the ends of branches; they are purple or pink, with a yellow center, and are pollinated by birds and insects. The fruit is a capsule, measuring 5-10 cm long, containing numerous seeds.",
